  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>De-link the <strong>mini cooking</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chorizo</strong> and cut them in half</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>rosemary</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from the stalks and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot (with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chorizo</strong> and <strong>onion</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook&nbsp;for 3-4 min or until the chorizo has released its oil and the onion has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Deseed the<strong>&nbsp;yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into small bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong>&nbsp;coarsely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rosemary</strong> to the pot and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for a further min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong>, <strong>conchiglie</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pasta</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> to the pot and give it a good stir&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cover and cook for 7-10 min or until the pasta is nearly cooked</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the<strong> cheddar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/474.step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the lid from the pot and continue to cook until most of the stock has evaporated, stirring continuously, until a sauce has formed and the pasta is cooked&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once reduced and thickened, remove from the heat and stir in the<strong>&nbsp;grated cheese</strong> and half of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;parsley</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
